<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 0 (10 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Charge.</em></strong> If the goat moves at least 20 ft. straight toward a target and then hits it with a ram attack on the same turn, the target takes an extra 2 (1d4) bludgeoning damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a DC 10 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone.</p>

<p><strong><em>Sure-Footed.</em></strong> The goat has advantage on Strength and Dexterity saving throws made against effects that would knock it prone.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Ram.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +3 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 3 (1d4 + 1) bludgeoning damage.</p>

